{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17613547","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17613547"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:36:36+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:36:36+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16317"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16317","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16317"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9008"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116128"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9008","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9008"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16317"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98124"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1992"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"5586"},{"type":"tags","id":"7518"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21437"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21441"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22682"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116128","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/116128"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe eye contains several distinct layers and structures that work together to enable vision. One of these layers lies between the retina and sclera.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the highly vascular layer that provides nutritional support to the outer retina?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Choroid","Cornea","Conjunctiva","Iris","Sclera"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Echoroid\u003C/strong\u003E is a highly vascularised layer located between the retina and sclera. It provides essential oxygen and nutrients to the outer layers of the retina. The choroid is part of the uveal tract, which also includes the iris and ciliary body.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esclera\u003C/strong\u003E is the tough, white, outer protective layer of the eye. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ecornea\u003C/strong\u003E is the transparent front part of the eye that covers the iris and pupil. The \u003Cstrong\u003Econjunctiva\u003C/strong\u003E is the mucous membrane that covers the front of the eye and inner surface of the eyelids. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eiris\u003C/strong\u003E is the colored part of the eye that controls pupil size. The choroid\u0027s rich blood supply is crucial for maintaining the health and function of the photoreceptors in the outer retinal layers.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The choroid is the vascular layer between the retina and sclera that provides oxygen and nutrients to the outer retinal layers.","The choroid is part of the uveal tract along with the iris and ciliary body."],"references":["Probst, L., \u0026 Tsai, J. (2024). Ophthalmology: Clinical and Surgical Principles. CRC Press","Salmon, J. F. (2024). Kanski\u0027s Clinical Ophthalmology E-Book: A Systematic Approach. Elsevier Health Sciences","Kels BD, Grzybowski A, Grant-Kels JM. Human ocular anatomy. Clin Dermatol. 2015 Mar-Apr;33(2):140-6. doi: 10.1016/j.clindermatol.2014.10.006. PMID: 25704934"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98124"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16317"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98124","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/98124"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-27T16:44:41+09:30","updatedAt":"